column13: Single cells were washed twice with 1x PBS containing 0.1% BSA before placing in lysis buffer.
column14: Single blastomeres were isolated by removing the zona pellucida using acidic tyrode solution (Sigma, cat. no. T1788), then separated by gentle mouth pipetting in a calcium-free medium.
column16: RNA was isolated from single cells or single morula embryos and amplified as previously described (Tang et al., 2010, Nat Protoc)
column17: Library construction was performed following Illumina manufacturer suggestions.
column20: Raw reads from the Illumina HiSeq2000 were mapped to the mm9 genome using default parameters in BWA
column21: Mapped transcripts reads were transformed using the reads per kilobase per million (RPKM) metric
column22: Genes with low expression in all stages (average RPKM<0.1) were filtered out, followed by quantile normalization.
